$spy $qqq $aapl $gld let me dissect this statement piece by piece; "another liberal state closed down hawaii". so in this fragmented sentence the writer is saying that some liberal state (unnamed) has closed down hawaii. "i thought warm weather killed it." is a question and not a statement. the writer here is asking for an answer. "it all the sanctuary states." here, this sentence uses the singular pronoun "it" as a replacement for the plural "states" and more worrisome is the fact that this "sentence" does not contain a predicate. lastly, stop politicizing this virus as if any party or political belief is responsible for who gets it!

it’ll be interesting to see what the reaction is to the “marshall plan” stimulus. on the one hand, yes we are bailing out companies and that should be a positive. 
on the other, it has to be questioned how effective a stimulus is when everything will continue to be shutdown for another month or two. it doesn’t really save the airline employees if the airlines remain empty. in fact it’s like burning/throwing cash at the problem. 

additionally, when i was studying the marshall plan in an advanced course on international economic theory, economists genuinely questioned whether the marshall plan was actually effective. i will have to dig out my old textbook on it and show the statistics.

$spy gap downs (probable monday) are great opportunities to win on both calls and puts intraday.👇

the past 4 gap downs looked like this

march 18: up right away to 50% retrace on pattern. fade back to below open after breakdown @10:50am.

march 16: up right away to 50% retrace on pattern. fade back to below open after breakdown @12:15pm

march 12: circuit breaker in first 5 minutes, down $3 to lows 3 mins later. retrace 50% of total loss on pattern. fade back below open on breakdown @ 11:00am

march 9: circuit breaker in first 5 minutes, down $4 to lows 3 mins later. retrace 50% of loss on pattern. fade back below open on breakdown at 12:16pm.

lesson: dramatic moves down in this obvious bear territory and high volatility gives the opportunity to make some nice gains on both the call and put day trade
